@page "/custom-themes"
<PageTitle>Custom Themes - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1>Custom Themes</h1>

<main class="documentation">

    <section class="card">

        <h2>Built-in Custom Themes</h2>

        <p class="subtitle">
            Saascade ships with several custom design systems that don't depend
            on any external CSS framework.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h3>Basic1</h3>
        <pre><code>builder.Services.AddSingleton&lt;IDesignSystem&gt;(DesignSystems.Custom.Basic1);</code></pre>
        <p>A minimal custom design system with basic styling.</p>

        <h3>Handdrawn</h3>
        <p>Three handdrawn variants are available:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>HanddrawnAssessible</strong> — accessible color palette with hand-drawn borders.</li>
            <li><strong>HanddrawnBlackAndWhite</strong> — monochrome hand-drawn aesthetic.</li>
            <li><strong>HanddrawnColor</strong> — colorful hand-drawn style.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Empty</h3>
        <pre><code>builder.Services.AddSingleton&lt;IDesignSystem&gt;(DesignSystems.Custom.EmptyDesignSystem);</code></pre>
        <p>A blank canvas — no classes applied. Useful for fully custom CSS.</p>

    </section>

</main>
